column5: I think that all involved did an exceptionally great job with all that was involved in making this change over!
Youse all did good...tells your mothers !
Rick, all that OT you've been putting in at time-and-a-half...  LOL  Really nice work.  Thank you and to everyone who's extra work makes this the place it is for us.  Cheers!
Well on your way to a kick-butt site already.  You guys put a lot of work into this and it shows.  Great job !

Well our first day in the new house and nothing caught fire or blew up. That's pretty much how I measure success  We set records all over the place. Just a titch under 60,000 page views...and around 3.0 Gb of data was transfered. 196 people on line at once!  That is crazy! I may have been a little short with people. I'm sorry for that. No excuses. We were kinda stressed today. We are slowly catching up on all the post transfer requests, so please be patient. It is likely that some got lost or overlooked in the chaos. When we have gone through all the PM's (I had over 100) we'll make a sticky for those who were forgot. We added Spell Check today and a weather module. The weather module is kinda sucky..but it was free. What I will do when I have more time is put in live satellite, radar and wind speed maps of MOST of Ontario. I haven't seen a view yet that covers the whole province, but I'll see if I can find zoomable ones. Now, if you'd like to see more features added, just ask. If it is possible, we will try and do it. I got to chat with old friends in the chat room and made some new ones. And that's what this is all about! Enjoy and keep checking back for some really cool prizes and contests. This whole thing is going to kick serious butt!
All i know.. is i need some sleepage... ta ta till tomorrow... wow.. what a day..
Good job boys! It was all that and then some ...nice work...those stats are SOLID no worries "respect due...."

Good job as usual guys, I do have one silly question though.  it says on the main page that 375 have registered, yet there are people with member numbers higher than that...like 384....can this thing count right ???  Maureen

Great Job guys....... I was having trouble getting access although I was logged in... seems Roy took care of that for me.... THANK YOU ROY...  Have a great weekend all, I'm off to BOQ...  yeeeehaaaaaa  Lady....
Great job guys, an amazing task
Yes a good job, thanks to all...
Good job indeed.
The new site is great.
Great job guys....all the work really is appreciated!!!!  dk
Can't agree more, great job guys   .  <----(that smilie makes me laugh) The new board is awesome.
Thanks Fellas.
Great job guys, everything is awesome!
Rick did you get the mind control program installed that will turn us all into consumers that will buy OFC stuff yet. Great job and thanks for all of the help.  Art
I stand and applaud all the hard work!!!  The weather module and spell check implementation were complete bonuses....I wasn't expecting any of those for at least a week.  Thank!!!

Fantastic job guys.  This continues to be the best site on the web. Rick, you can really turn some magic.  As an I.T. quality guy, I can't say enough about how smooth a transition this was. That's one of the problems, when everything goes the way its supposed to, with very little noise/issues, people don't realize just how successful that is. For you to be talking more features after Day 1 is just amazing!! Kudos my friends!!!!

Thanks for the words, folks. RICK is the guy who is building and fixing EVERYTHING. We have a great site here and with everyone's participation, it can only get even better. Thanks Rick and all the members.
I would just like to thank all those who are responsible for this great new site  Thanks Jason
Rick Rick Rick...  thats all I hear about..  I'm beginning to feel like the ugly Brady Bunch Daughter...  LOL
Congrats to all involved..... even the "geeky guy with glasses!"
Great job guys, esp. Rick. Very smooth, considering how much happened in just the day...  How long will it be before before the first tutu photo is posted?    Mike
I may have been a little short with people.  Only a little?......LOL   Good job guy's a job really well done..........
I'm glad my hard work paid off.
Best of all, you have cleaned the cobwebs so to speak with inactive members gone and probably not re-registering  Cheers, Tony

Thank you everyone for a superb job, all your efforts and the time you must have put into the new site is appreciated.  The new format is great and easy to drive around, and I'm sure will be a great success (already is!)   Mick
